# led-matrix-server runtime configuration.
#
# THIS IS A TEMPLATE. Copy it to led-matrix-server.conf (gitignored) and edit.
# The binary reads this file directly (next to it); there are no command-line
# arguments -- everything is set here.

# --- Panel geometry ---
# One 64x64 panel tile; 4 wide (chain) x 2 tall (parallel) => a 256x128 canvas.
LED_ROWS=64
LED_COLS=64
LED_PARALLEL=2
LED_CHAIN=4
LED_SLOWDOWN_GPIO=3

# --- HTTP control server ---
# Open http://<pi-ip>:8080/ in a browser for the mode menu + Lua textbox.
# The same port serves a JSON API: GET /api for state, POST /api {"mode":N}
# to switch (N 1-based; N=0 cycles), and POST /api/lua with a raw Lua script
# body to run it. This replaced the old telnet + Lua-upload TCP ports.
WEB_PORT=8080
# Optional HTTP basic auth for the whole web server. Empty/unset = no auth.
# WEB_AUTH=user:password
# Optional HTTPS. Set both to PEM paths to serve https:// instead of http://
# (needs a TLS-enabled binary: build with `make TLS=1`). Unset = plain HTTP.
# TLS_CERT=/root/led-matrix-server/cert.pem
# TLS_KEY=/root/led-matrix-server/key.pem

# --- Startup (optional) ---
# START_MODE  : mode number to start in (1-based; default 1)
# FPS         : target frames per second (default 60)
# SPEED       : animation speed multiplier (default 1.0)
# START_MODE=1
# FPS=60
# SPEED=1.0


# --- Panel calibration tool ---
# run-cal.sh runs panel-cal at this brightness (%). Full-white on all panels at
# full brightness can overdraw the PSU and brown out the Pi, so keep this low.
# ~20 is verified safe here; raise cautiously only if your supply has headroom.
CAL_BRIGHTNESS=20

# --- Jellyfin mode ---
# Your Jellyfin server (host:port) and an API key (Dashboard -> API Keys).
# Read from the environment by the app; kept here (not in the binary or repo).
JELLYFIN_HOST=your-jellyfin-host:8096
JELLYFIN_API_KEY=your-api-key
